description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a full time registered Band 6 nurse to join our stoma care team at the Luton and Dunstable Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, highly motivated individual who has experience with colorectal surgical nursing; with an interest to develop their skills and knowledge to become a stoma care nurse specialist. The individual will need to demonstrate excellent communication and organisational skills and the ability to work well within a team and autonomously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve working in partnership with patients, families and the Multidisciplinary Teams in the hospital and wider community, providing high quality, compassionate and expert stoma nursing care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We actively encourage development of our team and are looking for someone willing to access training opportunities within stoma care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Debra Schrader - Senior Stoma Care Nurse Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;debra.schrader@ldh.nhs.uk Telephone number01582 497091&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ring Monday - Thursday 8.00 am-4.00 pm&lt;/p&gt;
